Interesting results were obtained from optical measures for each conversion step, Fig. 6. Aiming to get good optical measurements, the deposition time for PbS thin films was 360 minutes, which produced films of approximately 750 nm. Thus, the thickness of PbI2 and perovskite films after the conversion becomes 1.3 and 2.3 µm, respectively. The band gap of deposited films was determined using the Tauc’s relation, Equation (1)64:1αhν=C(hν−Eg)n,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
