Band-gap calculation for the films at each step. (a) Tauc’s plot (where α = absorption coefficient, h = Plank’s constant and ν = frequency) indicating the band-gap of the film (dashed lines). The insets are pictures of the samples after each conversion step. (b) Absorption and photoluminescence of the perovskite film as a function of wavelength.
